53 Enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaranna>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/29/02 11:56:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dire Charm in the new planes?</span><hr size=1> You're overestimating the usefulness of Mana Burn.<br>
<br>
I think you'll see most wizards go for Spell Casting Fury Mastery before trying for Mana Burn now, just because it's so limited in its usefulness.<br>
<br>
I would like to see Enchanters get an upgraded Dire Charm, though.  I would also like to see Wizards get something to replace Nexus Gate, or remove the reuse timer on it.<br>
<br>
And don't say that quad kiting is too powerful.  Necromancers fear kite.  Mages have some pretty strong pets as well.  Enchanters have their own special kind of kiting that I don't even begin to understand.  But quad kiting is the way we wizards make up for not having pets.  We're supposed to be the &quot;masters of magical damage,&quot; and our most powerful damage spells are our AE spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oddlytwisted>Oddly Twisted</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/30/02 8:01:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dire Charm in the new planes?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> We're supposed to be the &quot;masters of magical damage,&quot; and our most powerful damage spells are our AE spells. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Jaranna, I completly agree.. But the fact remains Solo Charming in PoK is near impossible for an enchanter. The charms break so often and quick, and most of the mobs being just as fast as Sow it's like a death wish.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Enchanters have their own special kind of kiting that I don't even begin to understand <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The only Kite for an enchanter I can think of is stun kiting, but even now in PoK with Mobs doubling in the 300s, 1 resist of a stun and an enchanter becomes wet noodle being tossed into a fan blade.<br>
<br>
I can understand they do not want 60+ enchanters farming like they do now in Kael with Dire Charm and such, but there has to be some middle ground.<br>
<br>
