<br>
61 - Arcane Rune. I can't say enough good things about this spell. A 1500 point self only, componentless Rune spell with instant recast is godly when it comes to helping with charm breaks (you will save your cleric a huge amount of mana over the course of an evening). Sure in some PoP zones that's only 1-3 rounds of combat but that's maybe all you need to re-establish charm. This spell also stacks with Bedlam and the regular Rune series of spells and practically turns you into your own healer.<br>
<br>
61 - Boggle. Basically Concussion for enchanters<br>
and more reliable than memblur. Although kinda pricey in the mana department a 0.5 second casting time means you can hit this one as soon as charm breaks and there's a fair chance the mob will lose agro from you as long as you have someone else to dump the aggro on momentarily (although just like blur you have to be careful you don't end up with the cleric taking it when you drop down the aggro list).<br>
<br>
62 - Word of Morrell : point blank 6 second AE mez with 1.5 second casting time. I don't have this one yet but I can see how it would be useful as an effective replacement for the Color Stun spells that you can't use in much of PoP due to mob levels. Sort of half an upgrade to those stuns really. I say half because you get the breathing-space you'd get from using a PB stun, plus the ability to affect mobs over level 55 but this spell can't be used in AE groups.<br>
<br>
Total Domination - new enchanter AA. Each level of this reduces the chance of a charm break. I am probably going to go for this before Dire Charm.<br>
<br>
Combine all of the above with the regular stuff like root and mez and you have quite the package for handling charm breaks in the new planes.<br>
<br>
That said I still plan on getting DC at some point just because it's cool to be able to take afks when hunting without worrying that you will be murdered by an angry ex-pet, in the same way that i'd use an animation right now if i'm feeling lazy.<br>
